Risk Appetite:

the amount of risk that an entity is willing to accept

the owners or board of directors set the risk appetite for the company

this can also be delegated to senior management

translates into standards and policies to maintain risk at the level of the risk appetite










Risk Capacity:

is the amount of loss an enterprise can take without being in danger of closing

helps to set the risk appetite













Risk Tolerance:

the acceptable level of variation that management is willing to allow for any particular risk

this allows for occasional (and approved) deviations from the risk

the risk tolerance level is still under the risk capacity

defined at the enterprise level and reflected in policies













