Types of Changeover (implementation):

parallel changeover, a method where the old and new systems run simultaneously for a period until the new system is proven reliable

phased changeover, a method where the new system is implemented gradually in stages or modules while the old system is still in use

abrupt changeover, a method where the old system is completely replaced by the new system at once, often called a "big bang" approach











