Business Continuity Plans:

BCPs come out of the business impact analysis

the BIA establishes the recovery point objectives (RPOs) and recovery time objectives (RTOs)

environments with low RTOs have high availability systems

environments with low RPOs have high availability data architectures










Disaster Recovery:

disaster recovery refers to the recovery of business and IT services following a disaster

completed within a defined schedule and budget

flows from RTOs established by BIA and built into BCP

should be a primary and alternate for every activity











